{"title":"Salary Equivalence Calculator","description":"Find out how much you need to earn in a new city to maintain your current standard of living.","url":"https://urcity.com/tools/salary-equivalence-calculator/","content":"\u003ch2 id=\"salary-equivalence-calculator\"\u003eSalary Equivalence Calculator\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eMoving to a new city? Find out what salary you need to maintain your lifestyle.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"calculator-widget\" id=\"salary-calc\"\u003e\n  \u003ch3\u003eSalary Comparison Calculator\u003c/h3\u003e\n  \u003cdiv class=\"calc-row\"\u003e\n    \u003clabel\u003eCurrent Salary ($)\u003c/label\u003e\n    \u003cinput type=\"number\" id=\"current-salary\" value=\"100000\" min=\"0\" step=\"1000\"\u003e\n  \u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv class=\"calc-row\"\u003e\n    \u003clabel\u003eFrom City\u003c/label\u003e\n    \u003cselect id=\"from-city\"\u003e\n      \u003coption value=\"nyc\" selected\u003eNew York City\u003c/option\u003e\n      \u003coption value=\"sf\" \u003eSan Francisco\u003c/option\u003e\n      \u003coption value=\"la\" \u003eLos Angeles\u003c/option\u003e\n      \u003coption value=\"chicago\" \u003eChicago\u003c/option\u003e\n      \u003coption value=\"austin-tx\" \u003eAustin\u003c/option\u003e\n    \u003c/select\u003e\n  \u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv class=\"calc-row\"\u003e\n    \u003clabel\u003eTo City\u003c/label\u003e\n    \u003cselect id=\"to-city\"\u003e\n      \u003coption value=\"austin-tx\" selected\u003eAustin\u003c/option\u003e\n      \u003coption value=\"nyc\" \u003eNew York City\u003c/option\u003e\n      \u003coption value=\"sf\" \u003eSan Francisco\u003c/option\u003e\n      \u003coption value=\"la\" \u003eLos Angeles\u003c/option\u003e\n      \u003coption value=\"chicago\" \u003eChicago\u003c/option\u003e\n    \u003c/select\u003e\n  \u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cbutton class=\"btn btn-primary\" onclick=\"calculateSalary()\"\u003eCalculate\u003c/button\u003e\n  \u003cdiv class=\"calc-result\" id=\"salary-result\" style=\"display:none;\"\u003e\n    \u003cp\u003eYou need \u003cstrong id=\"needed-salary\"\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e in \u003cspan id=\"target-city-name\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e to maintain the same standard of living.\u003c/p\u003e\n    \u003cp id=\"salary-difference\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cscript\u003e\nfunction calculateSalary() {\n  const salary = parseFloat(document.getElementById('current-salary').value);\n  const fromCity = document.getElementById('from-city').value;\n  const toCity = document.getElementById('to-city').value;\n  \n  const colIndex = {\n    'nyc': 187.2,\n    'sf': 269.3,\n    'la': 173.3,\n    'chicago': 110.8,\n    'austin-tx': 119.3\n  };\n  \n  const cityNames = {\n    'nyc': 'New York City',\n    'sf': 'San Francisco',\n    'la': 'Los Angeles',\n    'chicago': 'Chicago',\n    'austin-tx': 'Austin'\n  };\n  \n  const neededSalary = Math.round(salary * (colIndex[toCity] / colIndex[fromCity]));\n  const diff = salary - neededSalary;\n  \n  document.getElementById('needed-salary').textContent = '$' + neededSalary.toLocaleString();\n  document.getElementById('target-city-name').textContent = cityNames[toCity];\n  \n  const diffEl = document.getElementById('salary-difference');\n  if (diff \u003e 0) {\n    diffEl.innerHTML = 'You would save \u003cstrong\u003e$' + diff.toLocaleString() + '/year\u003c/strong\u003e by moving.';\n    diffEl.className = 'savings-positive';\n  } else if (diff \u003c 0) {\n    diffEl.innerHTML = 'You would need \u003cstrong\u003e$' + Math.abs(diff).toLocaleString() + '/year more\u003c/strong\u003e to maintain your lifestyle.';\n    diffEl.className = 'savings-negative';\n  } else {\n    diffEl.textContent = 'Cost of living is roughly the same.';\n  }\n  \n  document.getElementById('salary-result').style.display = 'block';\n}\n\u003c/script\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"how-it-works\"\u003eHow It Works\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eEnter your current salary and city, plus your destination city. We calculate the equivalent salary using cost of living indices from official sources.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"example\"\u003eExample\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIf you make \u003cstrong\u003e$100,000 in New York City\u003c/strong\u003e, you need approximately \u003cstrong\u003e$62,000 in Austin\u003c/strong\u003e to maintain the same standard of living. That\u0026rsquo;s because Austin\u0026rsquo;s cost of living is 36% lower.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"data-sources\"\u003eData Sources\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eCost of living indices: Council for Community and Economic Research (C2ER)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eUpdated quarterly with the latest regional price parities\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"disclaimer\"\u003eDisclaimer\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThis calculator provides estimates for informational purposes only. Actual salary requirements will vary based on your specific lifestyle, household size, spending habits, and local market conditions. URCity and Northshore Press are not financial advisors, tax professionals, or career counselors. Always consult a qualified professional before making relocation or career decisions.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eLast updated: June 28, 2026\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n"}